<item>
            <title>[CXF-4762] HTTPS does not work with asynch client unless you specify port number </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-4762</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&#180;m trying to get CXF in combination with HttpAsyncClient to talk to my server over HTTPS. What I found is that when I try to consume the url &lt;a href=&quot;https://myserver/service&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://myserver/service&lt;/a&gt;, CXF/HttpAsyncClient will actually try to talk TLS to my server on port 80.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Digging around in various source code, I found that the getTarget() method in CXFHttpAsyncRequestProducer is a bit unfortunate. It seems to be hard coded to use port 80, unless a port is specified. I&#180;m suggesting that instead of hard coding port 80, CXFHttpAsyncRequestProducer should be looking at the scheme registry to find an appropriate port or just set the port to -1. In case it returns -1, HttpAsyncClient will do a lookup in the scheme registry to find default port for the requested scheme (ie. http=80, https=443)&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
